    "story":  [
                  "At the very summit, \u003cb\u003eQuince\u003c/b\u003e is grinding out 6 clean sheets like a man morally opposed to fun \u0026mdash; ugly, effective, and a touch boring. Hot on their heels, \u003cb\u003eBig Pewerk\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s lot have collectively decided defending is for cowards \u0026mdash; 25 goals banged in (GD +4), spearheaded by Switzerland (neutral, punctual and quietly annoying). Rounding out the smug end of the table, \u003cb\u003eSid\u003c/b\u003e is the undisputed sultan of the stalemate: 5 draws and counting. Edge-of-the-seat stuff it is not.",
                  "Wading into the midtable swamp, \u003cb\u003eEllie\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s backline has the structural integrity of a wet paper bag \u0026mdash; 28 shipped already, with Qatar (lavishly funded, modestly threatening) alone waving in 10. Keeping them grim company, \u003cb\u003eMurray\u003c/b\u003e is hauling Panama (spirited gatecrashers having the time of their lives) around like a dead fridge up a fire escape \u0026mdash; it\u0027s played, and contributed the square root of sod all. And clinging on by their fingernails, \u003cb\u003eIke\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s pride and joy is a tidy 3-0 spanking from France (world-beaters one dressing-room row from civil war) \u0026mdash; ruthless, efficient, faintly smug.",
                  "Down in the cheap seats, \u003cb\u003eElsa\u003c/b\u003e bagged the pasting of the tournament so far, Portugal (all flair, pout and theatrical collapses) romping home 5-0. Borderline rude. And scraping the very bottom of the barrel, \u003cb\u003eEtan\u003c/b\u003e watched Saudi Arabia (will park eleven buses and party at 0-0) get taken to the absolute cleaners 0-4 \u0026mdash; a scoreline best discussed in hushed, pitying tones."
              ],
